From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 14:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 33/64] web-app: Public Bots directory + Public Channels
 suggestions in New Chat

Two community suggestions below the New Group / New Channel entries of
the New Chat dialog:

- "Public Bots" opens a searchable directory of community-made bots
  (name, admin, description, language) loaded from
  github.com/deltachat-bot/public-bots. The first open asks for consent:
  the list is fetched from that third-party site, the bots are
  community-made and not checked/endorsed by us, and problems with a
  bot should be reported in that repo's GitHub issues. Picking a bot
  goes through the regular invite-link confirmation flow.

- "Public Channels" opens a dialog linking channel directories:
  arcanechat.me/channels, and fedimeteo.com under "More channels"
  (many cities already have their own weather channel there).

A "Hide community suggestions" switch (Settings -> Chats and Media)
hides both entries per user. Instance operators can hide them for
everyone (including the settings toggle) by setting
window.__slothfulConfig.hidePublicSuggestions, baked in via the
SLOTHFUL_HIDE_PUBLIC_SUGGESTIONS build/customize variable.
